  "body": "When using RPC node on Nethermind, we don't have an ability to know its health status.\r\n\r\nParity/OpenEthereum has a simple Health API to help sysadmin monitor node's status.\r\n\r\nIt works in a form of `parity_nodeStatus` RPC request: https://github.com/openethereum/openethereum/blob/ca3a82f3c417aa6e54b41f888198822ab15c004c/rpc/src/v1/impls/parity.rs#L464-L478\r\n\r\nIts response can also be got using HTTP request `/api/health`: https://github.com/openethereum/openethereum/blob/ca3a82f3c417aa6e54b41f888198822ab15c004c/rpc/src/lib.rs#L167\r\n\r\nIt gives `200 OK` status with `null` response result if the node has at least one peer and is not syncing.\r\n\r\nIf it loses peers, it returns `Node is not connected to any peers.`: https://github.com/openethereum/openethereum/blob/ca3a82f3c417aa6e54b41f888198822ab15c004c/rpc/src/v1/helpers/errors.rs#L514\r\n\r\nIf it is syncing, the response is `Still syncing.`: https://github.com/openethereum/openethereum/blob/ca3a82f3c417aa6e54b41f888198822ab15c004c/rpc/src/v1/helpers/errors.rs#L169\r\n\r\nPlease, add the same behaviour to Nethermind, but please also add one more kind of error:\r\n\r\nIf the node is turned on, but stopped handling blocks for some reason (i.e. it is red in Netstats and its last block number is not being increased), the error should look something like `Stopped handling blocks.`",
