    "body": "One more condition (for validator nodes only): it should return `Healthy` status (and 200 status code) if the node has at least 1 peer **AND** (is syncing **OR** already fully synced AND producing blocks).\r\n\r\nSo, if some validator stops producing blocks for some reason (because of some exception/error), but has peers and is fully synced, it should be treated as `Unhealthy` (and return 503 status code). And if the validator has peers and is syncing, it should be treated as `Healthy` (with 200 status code).",
